canonical_structure.name: UBX-RXM-MEASD12
canonical_structure.description: Satellite measurements for CloudLocate location service (first 12 bytes message)

fields.name: payload
fields.description: The message payload (first 12 bytes of the measurement set)

issues: Incorrectly identifies the payload length as variable 'N' when the message name (MEASD12) and description explicitly state it is a 12-byte message.

adjudication.reasoning: The UBX-RXM-MEASD12 message is part of a family of CloudLocate messages (MEASD12, MEAS20, MEAS50) where the suffix denotes the fixed byte length of the payload. Extraction 1 correctly identifies the fixed length of 12. Extraction 2 incorrectly defines the payload as variable length 'N', which contradicts the UBX protocol specification for this specific message ID (0x02 0x80).
